From `ih₂`:
`∀ (h₁ : (bs = [] → ns = [] ∨ ns.length = 1) ∧ (ns = [] → bs = [] ∨ bs.length = 1)), ¬{ lhs := b :: bs, rhs := ns, ok := h₁ } = nil → lengthSL (initSL ...) < ...`.

The goal is:
`⊢ (if h : ns = [] then splitInTwoSL (b :: bs) else { lhs := b :: bs, rhs := ns, ok := h₁ }).lhs.length + (if h : ns = [] then splitInTwoSL (b :: bs) else { lhs := b :: bs, rhs := ns, ok := h₁ }).rhs.length < (b :: bs).length + 1 + (n :: ns).length + 1`

